hashCode

public int hashCode()
Returns a hash code for this integer array. The hash code for a int [] object is computed as 
 arr[0]*31^(n-1) + arr[1]*31^(n-2) + ... + arr[n-1]
using int arithmetic, where arr[i] is the i th value of the integer array, n is the length of the array, and ^ indicates exponentiation. (The hash value of the empty integer array is zero.)
